<@U28TLDP0R> <@U33EGB4TX> <@U32LRG9NU> :

I just implemented a script that monitors youtube activity for folks we want to track and post
the idea is when one of these pops up we want to wrap it in a lightweight article that embeds the youtube video and tags the commanders discussed or viewed  in the video
so the long list above is becuase i just started the script
but from now on we’ll only see new videos
Sounds great. And this will be part of the "other" column we're planning on adding for non-hosted content?
yeah
Ok. Just wanted to clarify.
<@U28TLDP0R> : How do we differentiate/tag these “community” posts so they show up in the 2nd column?
I'll keep an eye out for this channel then. For the quick article do you guys think 300-500 words just highlighting a few of the sweet plays or a rundown of how a new commander might have played etc?
nah not even
basically embed video, tag commanders
Deal. That's much easier
maybe we can copy/paste their description?
That works.
include things like patreon links etc, that’ll make them happy
before we go balls to the wall on this i’d like to hear <@U32LRG9NU> opinion since he owns content.
Do you want me to use my own WP login for all of this too? Or is there a generic edhrec one I could use?
good question
using yours would make your page harder to see your real articles
like if i go to your user account
That's what I was thinking too
yeah i guess we can start a generic one
like edhrec-community i guess
Just edhrec-shared or something.
<@U3L7A68JC> has joined the channel
Community is better
should have invited henry
He'll get over it. Eventually
hehe
<@U32LRG9NU> should we link just videos for now or do other articles like Bennie/sheldon's stuff at scg, yours at GM etc
i’d like to do articles, but the automatic monitoring thing i need to write custom for that kind of stuff
i guess if you guys see something you want to share then you can do it
Ok. I know most writers we would want are pretty regular on their schedules anyways
yeah i guess if we just got together and started regularly linked to other people that would be good
again, wnt to see what jason says
they are differentiated by category
content v articles
<http://articles.edhrec.com/category/articles/>
<http://articles.edhrec.com/category/content/>
we apparently also have <http://articles.edhrec.com/category/news/> so that’s cool
Cool and then you just tell the columns to point at one or the other?
i deleted one of the entries to test that the script is running
should show up within 15 min
